'''Ivone Gebara''' (born 1944) is a Brazilian Catholic nun, philosopher, and feminist theologian.<ref name=Unisinos /><ref>[http://www.adital.com.br/site/noticia_imp.asp?cod=41869&lang=PT Ivone Gebara: Hierarquia da Igreja, obst<U+00E1>culo para empoderamento feminino]. ''Adital'', 9 de outubro de 2009.</ref><ref name=Teolog>[http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S0104-026X2006000100016&script=sci_arttext Teologia feminista e a cr<U+00ED>tica da raz<U+00E3>o religiosa patriarcal: entrevista com Ivone Gebara]. Por Maria Jos<U+00E9> Rosado-Nunes. ''Revista Estudos Feministas'', vol.14 n<U+00B0>1. Florian<U+00F3>polis, jan.-abr. de 2006. ISSN 0104-026X </ref>

Ivone Gebara was born in [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo]] on December 9, 1944<ref name="Notable 20th">{{cite book|last1=Fuertes|first1=Lizbeth Souza|title=Notable Twentieth-century Latin American Women: A Biographical Dictionary|date=2001|publisher=Greenwood Press|location=Westport, Conn. [u.a.]|isbn=978-0-313-31112-3|pages=110<U+2013>113|edition=1st|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=a7TY2ElIcrUC&lpg=PA114&ots=aqkGnbE5Yg&dq=Teresa%20Gisbert%20Carbonell%20de%20Mesa&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q&f=false|chapter=Ivone Gebara}}</ref> to a family of Syrian-Lebanese descent. After receiving a degree in philosophy, she joined the Augustinian Congregation of the Sisters of Our Lady in 1967<ref name="Notable 20th"/> at the age of 22. She earned a Ph.D. in philosophy from the [[Pontif<U+00ED>cia Universidade Cat<U+00F3>lica de S<U+00E3>o Paulo]].

Gebara taught at the Instituto Teol<U+00F3>gico do Recife (ITER) for almost 17 years alongside founder [[H<U+00E9>lder C<U+00E2>mara]]. Linked to [[liberation theology]], the institution existed from 1968 until it was closed by order of the [[Vatican]] in 1989.<ref>[http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/mundo/ft2404200514.htm Joseph Ratzinger esvaziou ala liberal no Brasil]. Por Frederico Vasconcelos. Folha de S. Paulo, 24 de abril de 2005.</ref><ref>TORRE,  Miguel A. de la (org)[http://books.google.com.br/books?id=Jj20KCZkZq8C&pg=PA28&lpg=PA28&dq=ivone+gebara+S%C3%A3o+Paulo+1944&source=bl&ots=QaA8SE2CxD&sig=7XFhWMNlvSCFTzF-PW0tP4Pd3gs&hl=pt-PT&sa=X&ei=G2h8UrCgC8mAkQeozICIDg&ved=0CGkQ6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=ivone%20gebara%20S%C3%A3o%20Paulo%201944&f=false The Hope of Liberation in World Religions]</ref> Since then she has devoted her time to writing and delivering courses and lectures around the world, on the foundations of religious discourse.

Since 1973 Gebara has lived in the [[Northeast Region, Brazil|Northeast Region]]. She currently lives in a poor neighborhood of [[Camaragibe]] in the [[Recife metropolitan area]], 25 km from [[Recife]].

In the 1990s, Gebara was tried and convicted by the Vatican for criticizing the moral teaching of the Church, especially due to comments she made in an interview printed in ''[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]]'' magazine in regard to [[abortion]].<ref name=Unisinos /><ref>[http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/mundo/ft1004200509.htm Papa silenciou progressistas brasileiros. Desarticula<U+00E7><U+00E3>o da ala da igreja identificada com a Teologia da Liberta<U+00E7><U+00E3>o se deu por meio da divis<U+00E3>o de arquidioceses e da censura]. Por Frederico Vasconcelos. ''Folha de S. Paulo'', 10 de abril de 2005.</ref> She was ordered to two years of [[forced silence]]. During that time, she obtained her second doctorate, in Religious Studies from the Catholic University of Louvain in Belgium. Gebara wrote a book addressing evil, ''Rompendo o sil<U+00EA>ncio: uma fenomenologia feminista do mal''.<ref name=Teolog /><ref>[http://www.dm.com.br/texto/99111  Igualdade dentro da igreja <U+00E9> desejada por religiosas. Mulheres participam de conclave, mas cozinhando, limpando e arrumando os aposentos dos cardeais.] Por Danilo, Boaventura. ''Di<U+00E1>rio da Manh<U+00E3>'', 11 de mar<U+00E7>o de 2013.</ref>

==Selected published works==
Gebara is the author of over thirty books and numerous articles published in Portuguese, Spanish, French, English and German.<ref>Nhanduti editora. [http://nhanduti.com/Gebara/Gebara_Ivone.Biografia.html Ivone Gebara.]</ref><ref name=Unisinos>[http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:NEPEfm4jIu4J:www.ihu.unisinos.br/noticias/511796+&cd=2&hl=pt-PT&ct=clnk&gl=br Uma clara op<U+00E7><U+00E3>o pelos direitos das mulheres. Entrevista com Ivone Gebara]. Por Mariana Carbajal. Instituto Humanitas - [[Unisinos]], 25 de julho de 2012</ref> Among her major works are:

*''Trindade: palavra sobre coisas velhas e novas. Uma perspectiva ecofeminista'' (1994)
*''Teologia ecofeminista. Ensaio para repensar o Conhecimento e a Religi<U+00E3>o'' (1997)
*''Rompendo o sil<U+00EA>ncio. Uma fenomenologia feminista do Mal'' (2000)
*''A Mobilidade da Senzala Feminina. Mulheres Nordestinas, Vida Melhor e Feminismo'' (2000)
*''La sed de sentido. B<U+00FA>squedas ecofeministas en prosa po<U+00E9>tica'' (2002)
*''As <U+00E1>guas do meu po<U+00E7>o. Reflex<U+00F5>es sobre experi<U+00EA>ncias de liberdade'' (2005)
*''O que <U+00E9> Teologia'' (2006)
*''O que <U+00E9> Teologia Feminista'' (2007)
*''O que <U+00E9> Cristianismo'' (2008)
*''Compartilhar os p<U+00E3>es e os peixes. O cristianismo, a teologia e teologia feminista'' (2008)
*''Vulnerabilidade, Justi<U+00E7>a e e Feminismos - Antologia de Textos'' (2010) 
*''Terra - Eco Sagrado (Teologia da Liberta<U+00E7><U+00E3>o e Educa<U+00E7><U+00E3>o Popular)'' (with Arno Kayser)

